&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;undiminished&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;undiminished&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; means not reduced or lessened. (अक्षुण्ण)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Despite the false allegations, the judge&amp;#39;s reputation remained intact or undiminished.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The other options: &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;damaged&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;illegal&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;uncertain&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; do not fit the context as appropriately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complete Sentence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The judge&amp;#39;s standing in the legal community, though shaken by false allegations of wrongdoing, remained &lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;undiminished&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Damaged (क्षतिग्रस्त)&lt;/strong&gt;: means harmed or injured.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Illegal (अवैध)&lt;/strong&gt;: means against the law or not allowed by law.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uncertain (अनिश्चित)&lt;/strong&gt;: means not known or not definite.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

Here the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Bases are bitter when they are tasted.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Some verbs if followed by adjectives, follow the given structure:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Active Voice - &lt;strong&gt;Subject + verb + adjective.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice - &lt;strong&gt;Subject + helping verb + adjective + when + it/they + helping verb + V&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;sub&gt;​&lt;/sub&gt;For Examples:-&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Quinine tastes bitter.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Quinine is bitter when it is tasted.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;They&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be used because bases act as a plural noun.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Are&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; will be used to qualify the plural noun.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct passive voice is&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Bases are bitter when they are tasted.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;कुछ &lt;strong&gt;verbs&lt;/strong&gt; यदि &lt;strong&gt;adjectives&lt;/strong&gt; द्वारा अनुसरण की जाती हैं, तो दिए गए ढांचे का पालन करें: -

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Active Voice -&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + verb + adjective.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Passive Voice -&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subject + helping verb + adjective + when + it/they + helping verb + V&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; bottom: -0.25em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;उदाहरण के लिए: -&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Quinine tastes bitter.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Quinine is bitter when it is tasted.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;They&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;का उपयोग किया जाएगा क्योंकि&lt;strong&gt; bases&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;बहुवचन संज्ञा के रूप में कार्य करता है।&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;बहुवचन संज्ञा को अर्हता प्राप्त करने के लिए &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;are&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;का उपयोग किया जाएगा।&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When&lt;strong&gt; reporting someone&amp;#39;s statement&lt;/strong&gt; in indirect speech, we &lt;strong&gt;usually change &lt;/strong&gt;the verb tense to reflect the shift in time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this case, &lt;/strong&gt;the original statement is in the present tense (&amp;quot;My parents are getting divorced&amp;quot;), so when we report it indirectly, we need to change the verb tense to past tense.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; correctly changes the verb tense to past tense, reflecting the shift from the original statement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;past progressive tense&lt;/strong&gt; (&amp;quot;were getting divorced&amp;quot;) &lt;strong&gt;indicates &lt;/strong&gt;an ongoing action in the past.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct sentence&lt;/strong&gt; is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Tina said that her parents were getting divorced&amp;quot;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;arbitrary&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains the role of the &lt;strong&gt;judiciary&lt;/strong&gt; in protecting constitutional principles and preventing misuse of power by the executive.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The blank describes the type of executive power that the judiciary safeguards citizens against.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Arbitrary&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means actions based on personal choice or whim rather than law or fairness, which can threaten individual liberties.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Thus, the phrase &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;arbitrary use of executive power&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; fits the context logically and grammatically.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 3&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Judicious (विवेकपूर्ण):&lt;/strong&gt; Means showing good judgment or wisdom. It does not fit the context because the sentence refers to misuse of power.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lawful (कानूनी):&lt;/strong&gt; Means permitted by law. The judiciary protects against misuse, not lawful actions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systematic (व्यवस्थित):&lt;/strong&gt; Means done according to a planned system. It does not convey misuse or abuse of executive authority.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;ensure&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the importance of &lt;strong&gt;judicial accountability and transparency&lt;/strong&gt; in maintaining fairness within the legal system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that transparent procedures help maintain &lt;strong&gt;fairness and impartiality in decision-making&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;ensure&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to make certain that something happens or is guaranteed, which logically fits the context of maintaining fairness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options such as &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;obstruct&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;complicate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;diminish&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; convey negative meanings that contradict the idea of promoting fairness and transparency.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Obstruct (बाधा डालना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to block or hinder progress. This does not fit the context of promoting fairness in judicial procedures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complicate (जटिल बनाना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to make something more difficult or complex. This contradicts the idea of transparent procedures improving fairness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diminish (कम करना):&lt;/strong&gt; It means to reduce or weaken something. This meaning does not align with maintaining fairness and impartiality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage explains the importance of an &lt;strong&gt;independent judiciary&lt;/strong&gt; and how its decisions influence public trust in the legal system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states that when courts deliver &lt;strong&gt;well-articulated verdicts&lt;/strong&gt;, they ______ confidence in the legal system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The verb should express the idea of &lt;strong&gt;strengthening or increasing trust&lt;/strong&gt; in the judiciary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Reinforce&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;to strengthen or support something&lt;/strong&gt;, which fits the context perfectly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options such as &lt;strong&gt;weaken, undermine,&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;question&lt;/strong&gt; convey negative meanings and contradict the positive context of increasing public confidence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weaken (कमज़ोर करना):&lt;/strong&gt; to make something less strong or effective.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Undermine (कमज़ोर करना / क्षति पहुँचाना):&lt;/strong&gt; to gradually damage or reduce the effectiveness of something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Question (संदेह करना):&lt;/strong&gt; to express doubt or challenge something.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the role of the judiciary and the problems associated with delays in the legal process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The sentence states: &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;Prolonged litigation can (4) ______ justice, making legal remedies ineffective for many citizens.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct word should indicate a negative effect caused by long legal procedures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Delay&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; fits best because prolonged litigation slows down justice, often making it ineffective. This aligns with the concept of &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;justice delayed is justice denied.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options like &lt;strong&gt;expedite&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;accelerate&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;clarify&lt;/strong&gt; convey meanings opposite or irrelevant to the context.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Option 4&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expedite (त्वरित करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To make a process happen faster or more efficiently. This contradicts the context of prolonged litigation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accelerate (तेज़ करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To increase the speed of something. This also implies speeding up the process, which does not match the negative impact described.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clarify (स्पष्ट करना):&lt;/strong&gt; To make something clear or easier to understand. This meaning is unrelated to the delay in judicial proceedings.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3 &amp;ndash; &amp;#39;sustain&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The passage discusses the role of the &lt;strong&gt;judiciary in maintaining democracy, justice, and public trust&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The final sentence emphasizes that courts must demonstrate &lt;strong&gt;integrity and competence to maintain or preserve their credibility&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Sustain&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;to maintain, preserve, or keep something continuing over time&lt;/strong&gt;, which fits the context of maintaining judicial credibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Other options such as &lt;strong&gt;jeopardize, diminish,&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;conceal&lt;/strong&gt; imply harming, reducing, or hiding credibility, which contradicts the positive context of the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jeopardize (खतरे में डालना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to put something at risk or danger, which contradicts the idea of maintaining credibility.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diminish (कम करना / घटाना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to reduce or make something smaller or weaker, which does not fit the intended meaning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conceal (छिपाना):&lt;/strong&gt; Means to hide or keep something secret, which is inappropriate in the context of transparency and trust in the judiciary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In the following items, each passage consists of six sentences. The first sentence (S1) and the final sentence (S6) are given. The middle four sentences in each have been removed and jumbled up. These are labelled P, Q, R and S. You are required to find out the proper sequence of the four sentences and mark accordingly on the Answer Sheet.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S1:&amp;nbsp;In ancient India the city of Ujjain was&amp;nbsp;quite famous.&lt;br /&gt;
P:&amp;nbsp;Here lived at one time the poet Kalidas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
Q:&amp;nbsp;He was a famous learned astronomer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
R:&amp;nbsp;And here also came and worked Raja Jai Singh of Jaipur.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
S:&amp;nbsp;It was always renowned as a seat of learning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
S6:&amp;nbsp;So one can see what a great love all who care for India must feel for this ancient city.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;SPRQ&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt; mentions that the city of Ujjain was quite famous in ancient India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt; explains that the city was renowned as a seat of learning.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt; mentions that the poet Kalidas lived in Ujjain at one time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt; states that Raja Jai Singh of Jaipur also came and worked in Ujjain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;Q&lt;/strong&gt; explains that Kalidas was a famous and learned astronomer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sentence &lt;strong&gt;S6&lt;/strong&gt; describes the love that all those who care for India must feel for this ancient city.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the sentences are put in this order, they form a coherent and logical paragraph about &lt;strong&gt;the city of Ujjain and its significance in ancient India as a center of learning and culture&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;option 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct paragraph&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;In ancient India the city of Ujjain was&amp;nbsp;quite famous.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;It was always renowned as a seat of learning.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Here lived at one time the poet Kalidas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;R&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;And here also came and worked Raja Jai Singh of Jaipur.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Q&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;He was a famous learned astronomer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S6&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;So one can see what a great love all who care for India must feel for this ancient city.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Sentences of a paragraph are given below in jumbled order. Arrange the sentences in the correct order to form a meaningful and coherent paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. Every morning he would go to the river and sit fishing there the whole day long.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B. With the money he got he would buy food for himself and go home.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C. An old fisherman could no longer go out to sea so he started fishing in the river.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D. In the evening he would sell whatever he had caught during the day.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The paragraph involves an old fisherman&amp;rsquo;s routine and the sentences need to be arranged to reflect his daily activities in a coherent manner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence C is the first sentence&lt;/strong&gt; as it introduces the fisherman and his situation:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;An old fisherman could no longer go out to sea so he started fishing in the river.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence A follows&lt;/strong&gt; as it describes his daily fishing routine:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Every morning he would go to the river and sit fishing there the whole day long.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence D is the third sentence&lt;/strong&gt; because it explains what he does with his catch:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;In the evening he would sell whatever he had caught during the day.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sentence B is the fourth&lt;/strong&gt; as it concludes with how he uses the money earned from selling his catch:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;With the money he got he would buy food for himself and go home.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct sequence is &lt;strong&gt;CADB&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coherent paragraph after rearrangement&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;An old fisherman could no longer go out to sea so he started fishing in the river. Every morning he would go to the river and sit fishing there the whole day long. In the evening he would sell whatever he had caught during the day. With the money he got he would buy food for himself and go home.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
